# SPHR Security Log — Caddy reverse proxy with AUTOMATIC free HTTPS.
#
# Caddy fetches and renews a free Let's Encrypt certificate for you — no manual
# cert steps. HTTPS is REQUIRED for PWA install ("Add to Home Screen") and for
# GPS / camera permissions to work on guards' phones.
#
# 1. Replace "your-domain.com" below with your real domain, OR a free subdomain
#    (e.g. from https://www.duckdns.org — "sphr-security.duckdns.org").
# 2. Point that domain's DNS A-record at your server's public IP address.
# 3. Make sure ports 80 and 443 are open on the server (firewall + cloud rules).
#
# Everything (the PWA + the /api backend) is served by the "web" container on
# port 80 internally, so Caddy just forwards all traffic to it.

your-domain.com {
    encode gzip
    reverse_proxy web:80
}
